<h3 id="pay-items-and-paid-breaks" sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="342">Pay items and paid breaks</h3>
<p sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="344">When you transfer registrations on the <strong sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="344">Approve</strong> page, pay items are generated. A separate pay item is generated for paid breaks.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="346">The pay rate for a paid break is determined by the pay type that is set up in the pay agreements for the break. Instead of using a pay type, you can set up the cost price per hour on the break for a defined date interval.</p>
