<h3 id="scenario-4-the-worker-clocks-in-late-and-clocks-out-after-the-planned-clock-out-time-during-an-overtime-period" sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="533">Scenario 4: The worker clocks in late and clocks out after the planned clock-out time during an overtime period</h3>
<p sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="535">The worker clocks in late at 09:30 AM and then, to compensate for his late attendance, he works overtime and clocks out at 05:00 PM. Because the worker came in late and compensated by working longer, the company doesn't want to grant the worker overtime pay for the hours that he worked between the planned clock-out at 03:30 PM and his actual clock-out at 05:00 PM, even though this period is defined as overtime in the time profile.</p>
<p sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="537">To handle this scenario, the absence code can be set up to reduce overtime hours by any hours of illegal absence that the worker has on the same day. Select <strong sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="537">Time and attendance</strong> &gt; <strong sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="537">Setup</strong> &gt; <strong sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="537">Groups</strong> &gt; <strong sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="537">Absence groups</strong>, and select the <strong sourcefile="articles/supply-chain/production-control/pay-based-on-registrations.md" sourcestartlinenumber="537">Deduct overtime</strong> check box to deduct overtime from hours of illegal absence.</p>
